article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 78, LIU Brooklyn 65
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Gordon Klaiber and Chad Timberlake combined for 35 points to lead Fairleigh Dickinson past Long Island 78-65 Thursday. It was the fifth straight win for the Knights (11-8, 8-2 Northeast Conference). Klaiber had 18 points and seven rebounds, while Timberlake chipped in 17 on 8-of-12 shooting and eight rebounds. Michael Peeples added 16 points and nine rebounds for the Knights. The Knights shut out the Blackbirds (6-12, 3-6 NEC) over the first three minutes, jumping out to a 10-0 lead. Esa Maki-Tulokas followed a layup by connecting on a 3-pointer to cut the Knights' lead to five, but FDU scored the next eight points to regain its double-digit lead. FDU led 43-25 at the half. The Blackbirds were able to cut the margin to 68-61 with 1:16 left to play on a 3-pointer by Eugene Kotorobai. But FDU extended its lead again as Peeples hit three free throws in 12 seconds and then scored four straight to end the game. The Knights shot 56 percent from the field while holding LIU to 31 percent. James Williams led the Blackbirds with 14 points, and Maki-Tulokas had 13.
